author: Jeff Geerling
description:
The number of Raspberry Pis orbiting the earth is about to increase.

Thanks to everyone who helped me make this video, over the past year! I learned a LOT (especially how much I don't know) about CubeSats, Ground Stations, amateur radio for space, and more.

Mentioned in this video:

  - SilverSat: https://silversat.org
  - Build a CubeSat: https://www.youtube.com/@buildacubesat
  - CubeSat TEMPEST: https://ethoslabs.space
  - Tim Fowler's CubeSat Collection on Level 2 Jeff: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=woO0w92YuC0
  - Saveitforparts: https://www.youtube.com/@saveitforparts
  - RASCube: https://www.robinson-aerospace.com
  - MySat: https://www.mysatkit.com
  - GASPACS: https://artsci.usu.edu/physics/gas/projects/gaspacs
  - Mark Rober's SatGus: https://space.crunchlabs.com
  - Astro Pi: https://astro-pi.org

Support me on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/geerlingguy
